Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo has postponed the recusal decision again. #eNCA's Michael Appel and Thulasizwe Simelane are at the inquiry. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo has again delayed his decision on whether he will remain as chairperson of the state capture inquiry. Zondo has postponed his recusal decision to Thursday. READ: Zondo delays recusal decision Zondo, was expected to announce his decision on Wednesday morning. Zuma says Zondo is biased and has created a persecutory environment. Watch the video above for more on this story.